ith the soft glow of the evening sun shining in through the windows. Takagi is sitting relaxed on the couch reading a book while little Chi plays on the floor nearby. The TV is on in the background, a nature documentary about baby animals is playing.\\r\\n\\r\\nChi glances up at the TV, her attention caught by the sight of a sleeping baby owl, nestled contentedly in its nest. \\\"Mama, I wanna be a baby too!\\\" she declares excitedly, turning to Takagi. \\\"It looks so nice to just sleep all day and not have to go to yucky kindergarten.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\nTakagi looks up from her book, a playful glint in her eyes. \\\"Oh? Does my little girl want to be a baby again?\\\" she says in a gentle, teasing tone. \\\"Why don't you try it and see how you like it?\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"Yeah!\\\" Chi exclaims, immediately getting into character. She crawls onto the couch and snuggles up against Takagi, making soft baby noises. \\\"Goo goo ga ga,\\\" she babbles.\\r\\n\\r\\nTakagi smiles and pats Chi's head soothingly, lulling her. \\\"That's right, just close your little eyes and sleep, my sweet baby girl,\\\" she says. Before long Chi is breathing softly, seemingly fast asleep on the couch.\\r\\n\\r\\nBut just a few moments later, a loud gurgling sound erupts from Chi's tummy, her eyes fly open again. \\\"Waah! Baby is hungry!\\\" she cries, immediately jumping up from the couch. She starts to toddle towards the kitchen but Takagi stops her.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"Ah ah ah, little babies can't walk, they have to crawl,\\\" Takagi says, an impish smile on her lips.\\r\\n\\r\\nChi gets down on her hands and knees and crawls across the floor, babbling. \\\"Goo goo ga ga, baby wants num-nums!\\\" As she reaches the kitchen, Takagi swoops her up into her arms.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"And babies can't talk either, isn't that right?\\\" Takagi says, booping Chi on the nose. Chi starts flailing her arms and making exaggerated baby noises, eliciting a laugh from Takagi.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"Oh, is baby hungry?\\\